Date Completed: Oct 2010
Language: C++  
Development Environment: Dev C++   	
Important features: Contains 2D graphics display (using PDCurses.lib);
                    pointers, function pointers

Simulation and graphical display (in the console) of an arrow stick for 
traffic advisers. 

Allows the user to choose the amount of amber lights (8-12).

Available patterns:
  - alternate the ends of the light bar
  - move left to right or right to left
  - move from the center and then outwards
